title: Spring Grove Cemetery Entrance, 4521 Spring Grove Avenue
description: Spring Grove Cemetery, 4521 Spring Grove Avenue, was dedicated in 1845. The main gateway is flanked by office buildings erected between 1853 and 1867. They are designed in a Norman Gothic style planned by the Cincinnati architect James K. Wilson. The picture is of the entrance from inside the gates.
rights: All rights reserved. Contact the CMC photo curator for copies or permission.
